		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Once you've read enough the first step is choosing an assembler.  I suggest using asm6 because it is wonderful! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> It was written by someone who wanted a different assembler than the ones provided and so he wrote his own... and <a href="http://home.comcast.net/~olimar/NES/" class="postlink">has shared it</a> freely with us!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" />   It can be easy to learn to use; read his README.TXT sometime. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

